## 📊 Database Schema

### 👤 User Model
```prisma
model User {
  id             String           @id @default(auto()) @map("_id") @db.ObjectId
  email          String           @unique
  password       String
  createdAt      DateTime         @default(now())
  typingSessions TypingSession[]
}

## ⌨️ TypingSession Model

model TypingSession {
  id              String           @id @default(auto()) @map("_id") @db.ObjectId
  userId          String           @db.ObjectId
  promptText      String
  typedText       String
  startedAt       DateTime
  finishedAt      DateTime
  createdAt       DateTime         @default(now())
  
  // ML Features
  avgDwellTime    Float
  avgFlightTime   Float
  typingSpeed     Float
  errorRate       Float
  backspaceCount  Int
  sessionDuration Float

  user            User             @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  keystrokeEvents KeystrokeEvent[]
}
🔑 KeystrokeEvent Model
prisma
model KeystrokeEvent {
  id          String         @id @default(auto()) @map("_id") @db.ObjectId
  sessionId   String         @db.ObjectId
  key         String
  keyDownTime DateTime
  keyUpTime   DateTime
  dwellTime   Int
  flightTime  Int?
  session     TypingSession  @relation(fields: [sessionId], references: [id])
}
🌐 API Documentation
Authentication Endpoints
Register User
http
POST /api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword"
}
Response:

json
{
  "id": "65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1",
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs..."
}
Login User
http
POST /api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "securepassword"
}
Get Current User
http
GET /api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
Typing Session Endpoints
Create Session
http
POST /api/session
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "promptText": "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog",
  "typedText": "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog",
  "keystrokes": [
    {
      "key": "T",
      "keyDownTime": 1678901234567,
      "keyUpTime": 1678901234620,
      "dwellTime": 53,
      "flightTime": null
    },
    // ... more keystrokes
  ]
}
Response:

json
{
  "id": "session123",
  "userId": "65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1",
  "avgDwellTime": 120.5,
  "avgFlightTime": 85.2,
  "typingSpeed": 180,
  "errorRate": 2.5,
  "backspaceCount": 3,
  "sessionDuration": 12.5
}
Dataset Export
Download ML-Ready Dataset
http
GET /api/dataset/export
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
Optional filter by user:

http
GET /api/dataset/export?userId=65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1
Response: CSV file with columns:


userId,avgDwellTime,avgFlightTime,typingSpeed,errorRate,backspaceCount,sessionDuration

🔄 ML Pipeline

┌────────────┐    ┌────────────┐    ┌────────────┐    ┌────────────┐    ┌────────────┐
│   User     │    │  Frontend  │    │  Backend   │    │  MongoDB   │    │    ML      │
│  Types     │───▶│  Captures  │───▶│  Extracts  │───▶│  Stores    │───▶│  Training  │
│            │    │  Keystrokes│    │  Features  │    │  Features  │    │            │
└────────────┘    └────────────┘    └────────────┘    └────────────┘    └────────────┘
       │                 │                 │                 │                 │
       │   Raw data      │  JSON payload   │  Processed     │  Export CSV     │  Model
       └─────────────────┴─────────────────┴─────────────────┴─────────────────┴────────▶
🚀 Installation
Prerequisites
Node.js 18+

MongoDB Atlas account

npm or yarn

Git

Step 1: Clone the Repository
bash
git clone https://github.com/your-org/keystroke-dynamics-app.git
cd keystroke-dynamics-app
Step 2: Backend Setup
bash
# Navigate to backend folder
cd backend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Create .env file
cp .env.example .env

# Edit .env with your credentials
# DATABASE_URL, JWT_SECRET, PORT

# Run Prisma setup
npx prisma generate
npx prisma db push

# Start backend server
npm run dev
Backend will run on http://localhost:5000

Step 3: Frontend Setup
bash
# Open new terminal, navigate to frontend
cd frontend/client

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Create .env file
echo "VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api" > .env

# Start frontend dev server
npm run dev
Frontend will run on http://localhost:5173

🔐 Environment Variables
Backend (.env)
env
# Database
DATABASE_URL="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/keystroke_db"

# Authentication
JWT_SECRET="your_super_secret_key_here_change_this_in_production"

# Server
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development
Frontend (.env)
env
# API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api

# App Settings
VITE_APP_NAME=Keystroke Dynamics
VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
📖 Usage Guide
1. Register/Login
Navigate to http://localhost:5173/register

Create an account with email and password

Login with your credentials

2. Take a Typing Test
You'll see a prompt: "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog"

Type the sentence in the textarea

The system automatically records every keystroke

Click "Submit" when finished

3. View Your Data
Each session is saved to the database

Features are automatically extracted

You can export all data as CSV for ML training

4. Export for Machine Learning
bash
# Using curl
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
     -o typing_data.csv \
     http://localhost:5000/api/dataset/export
